today was a treat! Filmed some fun hair content for @holtrenfrew and my mom washed my hair in a tiny sink 😮‍💨

Today is *10 years* since i posted my very first YT video 🥹🤯 I was 18 years old, completely obsessed with makeup and beauty gurus (shoutout juicystar07), and frankly, felt completely lost. I remember feeling desperate to find a passion that I could pour myself into. One thing I was sure of was that I had an unhealthy obsession with makeup and YT, so I decided to film my first video and I fell in love. One decade and 869 videos later, my love for YouTube (and this community!!!!!) is still going strong. 💕🥲

As I’ve said before, I am so proud of our little corner of the internet. Kinda wild how we’ve essentially grown up together (*tear*). Thank you thank you thank you for sticking around week after week 🥰

It’s been a minute since I formally introduced myself 👋🏻🥰

——
Hi! I’m Jamie 🫶.

I’m a Gemini sun/rising with a Leo moon ♊️♌️

I’m 29, born and raised in Montreal, Canada 🇨🇦. I am the youngest of three (I have two sisters!).

When I was 18, I decided to pick up a camera and film my first YouTube video. I had no idea that it would lead to a decade-long career! I’m very grateful for my 18-year-old self for being courageous enough to put herself out there 🥲. I have been a beauty and lifestyle content creator ever since 📸.

In 2021, I started my small business, 
Jamie Paige Doodles. I design stationery, stickers, and other cute things 🎨; it brings me lots of joy.

I love spending time with my cat (Gus), reading 3 books simultaneously, trying every creative hobby at least once, crocheting , listening to the same playlist over and over, quiet mornings, nature walks and very awkward dancing. 

I am still actively trying to find myself. 
It can get lonely and confusing, but I am choosing to trust the process and enjoy the ride. ✨
